❯ /model 
  ⎿  Kept model as Opus 4.7 (1M context) (default)

❯ In this Unity project, I want mesh slicing with arbitrary planes to be one of 
   the main features. In this session, please implement a feature that slices a 
   Mesh with an arbitrary plane.                                                
                                                                                
  Given a Mesh and a plane represented by Unity.Mathematics.Geometry.Plane, the 
   system should cut the mesh along the plane, split it into two separate       
  meshes, and generate caps to close the cut surfaces on both sides.            
                                                                                
  Please begin with a naive implementation and create appropriate tests for it. 
   Use Unity’s standard Test Runner to perform functional tests. In addition,   
  render the generated meshes in a scene using MeshRenderer components and      
  perform qualitative visual validation using your own (AI agent) visual        
  inspection.                                                                   
                                                                                
  Please also prepare high-load test cases that simulate practical real-world   
  usage scenarios. For example, continuously slice a reasonable number of       
  high-polygon meshes every frame and render them using MeshRenderer. Measure   
  and report the performance characteristics of these tests.                    
                                                                                
  After completing the baseline implementation and evaluation, begin            
  optimization work. At this stage, introduce technologies such as the Burst    
  compiler and Unity’s advanced Mesh API. Use the same high-load test cases to  
  verify and compare the performance improvements achieved through              
  optimization.                                                                 

